{
  "texts": [
    "To develop our prompting strategy, we first created a development set encompassing six diseases: acute bronchitis, hyperlipidemia, hypoparathyroidism, osteoporosis, RA, and viral hepatitis type A.",
    "These six diseases were chosen to represent a diverse spectrum of therapeutic areas.",
    "Case definitions and phenotype algorithms, detailed in Supplementary Table 3 and Supplementary Note 1, respectively, were employed to identify cases within the Clinformatics® database.",
    "A non-random sample of 358 patients was selected by manual review, emphasizing challenging cases (cases that neither had all markers of a case nor no markers).",
    "The gold standard was created by a single reviewer using the KEEPER output as well as any other data available in the CDM."
  ]
}